Here's what you need:

## XAML

```xml
<RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
             Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">
    <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                    SelectionMode="Single"
                    SelectedItem="{Binding CurrentItem, Mode=TwoWay}"
                    SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}">
        <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
            <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Item">
                <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="Auto,*">
                    <Image Source="{Binding Icon}"
                           WidthRequest="40" HeightRequest="40" />
                    <Label Grid.Column="1"
                           Text="{Binding Name}"
                           VerticalOptions="Center" />
                </Grid>
            </DataTemplate>
        </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
    </CollectionView>
</RefreshView>
```

## ViewModel Bindings

You need four bindable properties/commands:

| Property | Type | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `Items` | `ObservableCollection<Item>` | Data source — use `ObservableCollection`, not `List`, so UI auto-updates |
| `CurrentItem` | `Item` | Bound `TwoWay` to `SelectedItem` — holds the selected object |
| `IsRefreshing` | `bool` | Bound `TwoWay` to `RefreshView.IsRefreshing` — set `false` when done |
| `ItemSelectedCommand` | `IAsyncRelayCommand` | Fires on selection change — navigate here |
| `RefreshCommand` | `IAsyncRelayCommand` | Fires on pull-to-refresh — reload API data here |

## ViewModel (using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm)

```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IApiService _api;
    private readonly INavigationService _nav;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private ObservableCollection<Item> items = new();

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Item? currentItem;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool isRefreshing;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task ItemSelectedAsync()
    {
        if (CurrentItem is null) return;
        await _nav.GoToAsync("DetailPage", new Dictionary<string, object>
        {
            { "Item", CurrentItem }
        });
        CurrentItem = null; // reset so the same item can be re-selected
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task RefreshAsync()
    {
        try
        {
            var data = await _api.GetItemsAsync();
            Items = new ObservableCollection<Item>(data);
        }
        finally
        {
            IsRefreshing = false; // MUST set false or spinner hangs
        }
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- **Reset `CurrentItem` to `null`** after navigation so the same item can be tapped again.
- **Set `IsRefreshing = false`** in a `finally` block — if you forget, the refresh spinner never stops.
- Use `ObservableCollection<T>` — a `List<T>` won't trigger UI updates on add/remove.
- Set `x:DataType` on the `DataTemplate` for compiled bindings.
